Job Summary

Our client in Financial Services aggressively going though digital transformation.
We are seeking for a competent Application Analyst for Oracle Data Stores.

Mandatory Skill-set

Diploma/Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or Computer Engineering;
At least 3 years of experience in Oracle databases and RDBMS concepts;
Hands on in development using Oracle SQL & PL/SQL;
Good experience in Oracle E-business Sub-ledger Accounting / SLA, Financial Accounting Hub / FAH, General Ledger / GL data structures and their relationships;
Must have experience working with cross functional teams;
Adept in leveraging latest technologies, best practices and lead in formation of effective solutions;
Excellent command over verbal/ written English and presentation to engage various stakeholders;
Organised and positive working attitude, with the ability to work independently and as a team.

Desired Skill-set

Agile / SCRUM Certified.

Responsibilities

Responsible for maintenance and enhancement of existing Oracle Data Stores;
Act as the Subject Matter Expert for Data Warehouse solutions along with data import from flat files to Oracle and vice versa;
Participate in various data mapping initiatives related to Oracle Data warehouse;
Collaborate with IT Application , Infrastructure and business teams to deliver effective solutions;
Maintain project documentation and track the changes;
Adhere to operation processes and procedures along with quality and timelines of deliverables;
Work with various vendors to maintain the SLA and assess root cause for remediation of issues.
